<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-59331" number="67319" version="3">
			<HEADING>Chapter 48: Elevator Violation Referrals</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-8227" name="T28C048"/>Chapter 48: Elevator Violation Referrals</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-109845" number="67320" version="2306">
								<HEADING>§ 48-01 [Elevator Violation Referrals.]</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-8229" name="T28C048_48-01"/>§ 48-01 [Elevator Violation Referrals.]</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59333" number="67321" version="726">
									<PARA>Upon referral to the Department by the Department of Buildings of an immediately hazardous elevator violation in a multiple dwelling which has not been corrected by the owner at the time of such referral, the Department will attempt to evaluate such violation based upon information provided to it by the Department of Buildings and from any other source, to determine what action may be taken by the Department. Such determination may be based upon the following criteria: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59334" number="67322" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Whether the dwelling units in the multiple dwelling are serviced by any other operable elevator, as determined by the Department of Buildings; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59335" number="67323" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The status of any criminal court enforcement action taken by the Department of Buildings or enforcement actions taken by the Department regarding elevators against the owner of the multiple dwelling that is the subject of the referred immediately hazardous elevator violation; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59336" number="67324" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any active work at the multiple dwelling, with respect to the immediately hazardous elevator violation as observed by the Department of Buildings during reinspections; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59337" number="67325" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(4)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Data reflecting elevator applications, to the extent that an application is required to be filed, and elevator building notices for the multiple dwelling, including date and application number; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59338" number="67326" version="1867">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(5)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Whether the owner of the multiple dwelling has a contract for repair of elevators as required pursuant to Administrative Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="28-304.7" destination-id="0-0-0-0">28-304.7</LINK>; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59339" number="67327" version="1867">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(6)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Data related to all reinspections with respect to the immediately hazardous elevator violation pursuant to Administrative Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="28-219.2.2" destination-id="0-0-0-0">28-219.2.2</LINK>, including inspection date, inspection result, violation numbers (where applicable), and inspector comments; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59340" number="67328" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(7)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any other information that the Department obtains regarding the immediately hazardous violation and the status of the repair of such violation. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59341" number="67329" version="126">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 5/27/2016, eff. 6/26/2016) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-59342" number="67330" version="1167">
								<HEADING>§ 48-02 [Department Actions.]</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-8231" name="T28C048_48-02"/>§ 48-02 [Department Actions.]</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59343" number="67331" version="726">
									<PARA>The Department may take such actions as it determines are necessary to address the referred immediately hazardous elevator violation, including, but not limited to, ordering the owner to correct such referred violation, performing the work to correct such referred violation, and taking enforcement action against the owner of the multiple dwelling that is the subject of such referred violation. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-59345" number="67332" version="126">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 5/27/2016, eff. 6/26/2016) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-002]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>